        <a title="Joanna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Joanna" href="/user/show/620387-joanna">Joanna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9781561008797" href="/book/show/980535.Two_or_Three_Things_I_Know_for_Sure">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/620387-joanna?shelf=2013-read">2013-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/620387-joanna?shelf=audiobooks">audiobooks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/620387-joanna?shelf=rws-2013-spring">rws-2013-spring</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer45514360" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12741783542010820077">Powerful and compelling autobiography. Having the author read this work herself for the audio version (on cassette!) really brought the short work to life for me. She was able to pack so much emotion into this telling and to really highlight the repetition of the &quot;two or three things I know for sure&quot; theme. If only I knew anyone else who still listened to cassettes, I&apos;d send this along to share it. Alas, I must be one of the last people out there who still has a cassette deck in the car and does</span>
  <span id="freeText12741783542010820077" style="display:none">Powerful and compelling autobiography. Having the author read this work herself for the audio version (on cassette!) really brought the short work to life for me. She was able to pack so much emotion into this telling and to really highlight the repetition of the "two or three things I know for sure" theme. If only I knew anyone else who still listened to cassettes, I'd send this along to share it. Alas, I must be one of the last people out there who still has a cassette deck in the car and doesn't mind pulling out the old tapes once in a while.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12741783542010820077" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

