<div id="review_2773122054" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2773122054" />
    <a title="Eric Cepela" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/72837849-eric-cepela"><img alt="Eric Cepela" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1508806861p2/72837849.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2773122054?book_show_action=true">Apr 09, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Eric Cepela" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Eric Cepela" href="/user/show/72837849-eric-cepela">Eric Cepela</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/8133912-two-or-three-things-i-know-for-sure">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2773122054" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9269456162502364150">this is a choppy mess that shouldn&apos;t have been published. hugely disappointing after reading Bastard Out of Carolina. it&apos;s supposed to be about storytelling, but she never finishes a story. there&apos;s even a quote that says, &quot;telling the story all the way through is an act of love.&quot; that&apos;s one of the two or three things she knows, which is a nonsense device. <br/><br/>1 star</span>
  <span id="freeText9269456162502364150" style="display:none">this is a choppy mess that shouldn't have been published. hugely disappointing after reading Bastard Out of Carolina. it's supposed to be about storytelling, but she never finishes a story. there's even a quote that says, "telling the story all the way through is an act of love." that's one of the two or three things she knows, which is a nonsense device. <br /><br />1 star</span>
